<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469758>
    dc:description "Figure 16. Habitus of C. wendti and variability of the dorsal plate sculpturing (PCM, females in dorsolateral view): A, neotype (population NO.448); B, population GB.097; C, population GL.044; D, population IS.013. Quadrangular frame delineates a place where epicuticular granules are atypically merged. Scale bars in μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469758/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469760>
    dc:description "Figure 17. Habitus of C. wendti and variability of the dorsal plate sculpturing (PCM, females in lateral view): A, population GB.097; B, population NO.246. Scale bars in μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469760/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469762>
    dc:description "Figure 18. Habitus of C. wendti and variability of the dorsal plate sculpturing (PCM, female in dorsal view, population PL.376). Scale bar in μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469762/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10492219>
    dc:description "Figure 19. Habitus of C. wendti (SEM, female in dorsal view, population IS.013). Scale bar in μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10492219/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469726>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Intracuticular pillars typical for the endocuticular plate structure in the Claxtonia wendti morphotype (PCM, on the example from the population NO.246). Scale bar in μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469726/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469764>
    dc:description "Figure 20. Detailed morphology of C. wendti: A, sex unidentified, lateral view (SEM, population IS.013, arrowhead indicates spine I); B, anterior body portion (SEM, population IS.013); C, snout and peribuccal appendages (SEM, population IS.013); D, claws I (PCM, population NO.246, arrowhead indicates spine I); E, claws II (PCM, population NO.246). Scale bars in μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469764/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10469737>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Variability in the development of spine on the first pair of legs in Claxtonia (PCM, on the example of the population NO.246). Scale bars in μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10469737/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

